'''The Alliance for Human Research Protection (AHRP)''' is [[Nonprofit organization|non-profit]] and [[tax-exempt organization]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://ahrp.org/category/board-of-directors/|title=Board of Directors Archives - AHRP|website=AHRP|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref> with a group of professional people who aim: to develop practices of ethical medial research<ref name=":0" /> to minimize the risks related to those practices<ref name=":0" /> and to ensure the protection of human rights, welfare, and dignity<ref name=":0" />

== Contribution ==
The AHRP raises public awareness about the issue through educational campaigns; informing research subjects about their rights; alerting the media; politicians; and concerning groups about the situation.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Singh |first1=Jatinder |title=Alliance for human research protection |journal=Journal of Pharmacology & Pharmacotherapeutics |date=2011 |volume=2 |issue=3 |pages=212–213 |doi=10.4103/0976-500X.83299 |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3157144/ |accessdate=6 August 2018 |issn=0976-500X}}</ref>

